        public String getCurrentCommit()

      • getConflicts

        public Collection<File> getConflicts()
        If the rebase started but was unable to finish because of unresolved conflicts then the method returns a collection of such files in conflict. To complete the rebase you need to resolve the conflicts and continue the rebase.
        Returns:
        files in conflict

      • getFailures

        public Collection<File> getFailures()
        When the rebase fails because of local modifications (i.e. it finishes with GitRebaseResult.RebaseStatus.CONFLICTS or GitRebaseResult.RebaseStatus.FAILED) then this method returns a collections of files causing the failure.
        Returns:
        files that cause the rebase to fail.
